        <mxCell id="footer-note" value="WHAT CHANGED vs Shepard_Database_Setup.drawio:&#10;&#10;(1) Linear :Predecessor chain (red bold arrows) replaces the parallel-tree-under-root shape.&#10;    Each step's temporal predecessor is explicit; the docket-root keeps CHILD_OF edges for navigation only.&#10;&#10;(2) post_analysis is its own :DataObject per step (green box in row 4) — not a JSON section nested inside the step.&#10;    On PA-Pyrolysis(2) we show what this unblocks: a :StructuredDataReference for the metadata PLUS&#10;    :FileReference peers for actual CT and Mikrometer artefacts. JSON-only PAs (the other 4) work too.&#10;&#10;(3) Editor stamps become :Activity nodes (pink) with PROV-O edges:&#10;       GENERATED → the step or PA DO  (dashed red)&#10;       WAS_ASSOCIATED_WITH → :User    (dashed yellow)&#10;    sourceMode = &quot;human&quot; encodes the f(ai)²r triad; a future AI-assisted edit would carry sourceMode = &quot;ai&quot;.&#10;&#10;Cross-step semantic vocabularies (Fiber Material, Weave, Precursor, Additive) live in :SemanticRepository and are linked&#10;via :SemanticAnnotation on the structure DO (not shown in this diagram for clarity — see findings §3 of the BTKVS-DOCKET-SHOWCASE doc)." style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=10;fillColor=#F5F5F5;strokeColor=#666666;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="1340" width="1500" height="180" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
